        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26052",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "name": "yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "displayName": "old of Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello, Benoit.\nhttp:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.rest.client.html\n\nIn 37.2.3. Request Arguments,  I can expect as following.\nThe string , \"method=arg&arg1=value1&arg=value1&arg2=value2\" is made from $client->arg('value1')->arg2('value2')->get() .\n\nDo you mean a string  , \"method=arg&arg0=value1&arg=value1\" should be made from $client->arg('value1')->get()  ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "name": "yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "displayName": "old of Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-12T05:28:21.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-12T05:28:21.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26056",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beau",
                        "name": "beau",
                        "displayName": "Benoit Aubuchon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello!\n\nSorry I should have put more details \n\nCurrently $client->arg('value1')->get(); gives method=arg&arg1=value1 and it should be method=arg&arg0=value1 because of the way Zend_Rest_Server builds the arguments list.\n\nThe problem arise when the server-side method have the first argument of the function optional. When Zend_Rest_Server builds the arguments list used to call the function, the first argument's value becomes the default one (Zend\/Rest\/Server.php:167) and a second argument gets created because of arg1 passed in the query (Zend\/Rest\/Server.php:174). If the argument was named arg0 it would overwrite the default value.\n\nI can send you a complete example if needed.\n\nBen",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=beau",
                        "name": "beau",
                        "displayName": "Benoit Aubuchon",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-12T06:28:53.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-12T06:28:53.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26438",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "name": "yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "displayName": "old of Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hello, Benoit.\n\nI think there may be problem in Zend_Rest_Server rather than Zend_Rest_Client.\n\nBecause the number of arguments should be started from 1.\n\ncf. the item \"Numeric index\" of http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.rest.server.html\n\nAnyway, I will research more detail on handle() function of Zend_Rest_Server.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "name": "yoshida@zend.co.jp",
                        "displayName": "old of Satoru Yoshida",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-11-16T21:53:28.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-11-16T21:53:28.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/26517",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "This would be a backwards compatibility breakage to change at this point. While cardinal numbers should have been used in the original implementation, they were not, and changing them at this point would break functionality for those using the server.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
